Class MetaDef.Object

Enclosing class:
MetaDef
public static class MetaDef.Object
extends MetaDef.Content

An Object is a single instance of an Element type. Objects have an identifying name and a type. The name identifies the object within its Element and must be unique within the Element. The object is itself an instance of an Element, and this Element is identified by the type. The type may be the type name of an Element or the class name of a Class.
